{{Infobox company | name = VectorCell | website = http://www.vectorcell.com | logo = vectorcell.gif | type = [[Privately held company|Private]] | foundation = 2005 | defunct = 18 November 2013 | location = [[Villebon-sur-Yvette]], [[France]] | key_people = [[Paul Cuisset]] | industry = [[Video game industry]] | products = [[Video game]]s }}
'''VectorCell''' was a [[France|French]] [[video game developer]] founded in 2005. The company was owned by [[Paul Cuisset]] and Lexis Numérique. The company developed ''[[Amy (video game)|Amy]]'' for [[PlayStation 3]] and [[Xbox 360]]. The company also planned to release Jesus Christ Super-Star on the iOS and Zeebo.
Previous releases include ''[[Mr Slime]]'' released under the Lexis Numérique label and published through [[SouthPeak Games]] in 2008.
In January 2010, VectorCell bought a licence for the Lightsprint middleware for realtime [[global illumination]].<ref>[http://www.lightsprint.com/ Lightsprint], news section</ref>
By the lack of success of the [[Flashback (2013 video game)|Flashback remake]], the company suffered from the same fate as [[Delphine Software International]] and closed down on 18 November 2013 after [[bankruptcy]] and [[liquidation]].
